summary: Justin Jefferson has signed a record-breaking four-year, $140 million contract extension with the Minnesota Vikings. The Vikings expressed their excitement at signing Jefferson, calling the deal a reflection of his exceptional talent and their commitment to building a strong team. The contract makes Jefferson one of the highest-paid wide receivers in the NFL, with an annual salary of $35 million. The Vikings believe the extension is a wise investment, given Jefferson's impressive performance and potential for continued success. The media widely praised the contract, recognizing Jefferson's achievements and the Vikings' smart move in securing his long-term presence on the team.

name: Djokovic
summary: Novak Djokovic's French Open journey has been marked by both triumphs and setbacks. He initially showcased resilience by overcoming Lorenzo Musetti and Francisco Cerundolo in five-set matches, despite raising concerns about his fitness after the latter victory. However, his title defense came to an abrupt end when he withdrew from the quarterfinals due to a meniscus tear in his right knee. This withdrawal also meant Djokovic would miss the 2024 French Open. Despite his injury, Djokovic expressed gratitude for the tournament's extended finish, which he believed galvanized him as the world's number one tennis player.

name: Dow Jones
summary: The stock market experienced significant declines over the past several days. The Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA) witnessed a drop of 1,000 points in the span of three days. S&P Global (S&P) reported an issue with its market data for the S&P and Dow Jones indices, which has since been resolved. The DJIA underperformed the S&P 500 index significantly, marking the largest gap between the two in a year. Stocks closed lower, with the DJIA losing over 300 points as Salesforce shares plummeted 20%. On June 3, 2024, the Nasdaq Composite Index rose while oil and Treasury yields fell. The Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA) dropped 411 points as UnitedHealth Group's stock value declined. Other market news for the same day included a DJIA decline, and significant movements in the stocks of GameStop, AMC, Nvidia, DJT, and Paramount. On May 30, 2024, the Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA) shed 330 points, and Salesforce's stock performance contributed to the decline. Furthermore, Dow Jones futures experienced a decline as Salesforce's stock plunged following a broader market slide. On May 29, 2024, the Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA) lost 400 points amidst rising Treasury yields and gains in Marathon Oil shares.

A research study has highlighted the underestimated potential for flooding in California in the future. Lastly, a film review describes an apocalyptic epic with a slow start but a powerful ending.

name: United Airlines passengers sick
summary: Several passengers on a United Airlines flight from Vancouver to Houston experienced unexplained illnesses during the flight. The passengers had disembarked from a cruise ship prior to boarding the plane. Medical officials suspect norovirus, a highly contagious gastrointestinal illness, may be the cause of the illnesses. The affected passengers were treated upon arrival in Houston and the plane underwent deep cleaning. The total number of passengers who fell ill varied in the news reports, ranging from two dozen to over 30.
